The paper deals with the computational complexity of Braid, a puzzle game, and shows that it can simulate an arbitrary computation. This suggests that the paper may belong to the computational complexity (cs.CC) or programming languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses technical lemmas about Turing machines, which may suggest it belongs to the graph theory (cs.GT) or data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the undecidability of Braid, which may suggest it belongs to the logic in computer science (cs.LO) sub-category.
